      <h2>ETWS Architecture Overview</h2>
      <p>The ETWS architecture consists of multiple components that work together to ensure messages reach mobile users quickly and efficiently.</p>

      <h3>Components</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cell Broadcast Center (CBC)</strong> - Generates the alert message.</li>
        <li><strong>Mobile Management Entity (MME)</strong> - Handles communication with the eNodeBs.</li>
        <li><strong>eNodeB</strong> - Base stations that broadcast the alert to users in the affected area.</li>
        <li><strong>User Equipment (UE)</strong> - Mobile devices that receive the alert.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Architecture Diagram</h3>
      <img src="etws-architecture.png" alt="ETWS Architecture Diagram" class="diagram">

